  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to quickly switch accounts from an account details page so that I can view the other account without having to go back to my wallet home.\r\n\r\n#### Depends on: #17367\r\n\r\n### Design\r\n\r\n[Link to Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/HKncH4wnDwZDAhc4AryK8Y/Wallet-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=838%3A216053&mode=design&t=CludiQ8UQRyvn76P-1)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"562\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19339952/fb120da7-9f0e-4ddc-892d-d912c3fe633a\">\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n- On tap of Account Avatar (on the right icon) of the navigation bar, the bottom sheet should open\r\n- The bottom sheet should display the accounts list with the `Select account` section header under the account quick actions\r\n- Upon scrolling, the account's quick actions should be sticky on top\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n- Use mock data to populate the list of accounts\r\n- On tapping an account, display an alert with the selected account ID or name\r\n- The account detail page doesn't have to change/update\r\n",
